The Limpopo man approached Oscar Pistorius &amp; claimed he could make his case go away for a fee of R250,000. JOHANNESBURG - A Limpopo man who posed as a National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) official trying to scam Oscar Pistorius has been sentenced to four years behind bars for corruption.Tshifhiwa Radzhadzhi was sentenced in the Specialised Commercial Crimes Court in Pretoria on Monday.Radzhadzhi was arrested in March after approaching Pistorius and claiming he could make his case go away for a fee of R250,000.The Hawks' Robert Netshiunda says, The 33-year old also had an eight-year sentence suspended for four years by a court in Pretoria. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)